      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/code-verification-mrl2",
      "rationale": "Code verification completed via ANSYS published benchmark suite including lid-driven cavity, backward-facing step, and rotating disk flows. Convergence to analytical solutions confirmed for all relevant physics. Gradation 2 achieved: independent benchmark results documented and traceable."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/discretization-error-mrl2",
      "rationale": "Mesh refinement study performed on three grid levels (2.1M, 5.8M, 14.2M cells). Grid convergence index (GCI) computed per Roache methodology. However, the fine-grid GCI for hemolysis index at the critical 4500 RPM / 5 L/min operating point is 8.3%, exceeding the required threshold of 5% for Gradation 3. The coarse-to-medium refinement ratio yields an apparent order of accuracy of 1.4, below the nominal scheme order of 2, indicating insufficient asymptotic convergence. Gradation 2 achieved (systematic mesh study with GCI reported) but Gradation 3 required (GCI < 5% with demonstrated asymptotic convergence). This factor is below required level and is the primary basis for rejection."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/test-conditions-mrl2",
      "rationale": "Experimental test conditions documented with calibrated flow meters (±0.5% FS), pressure transducers (±0.25% FS), and rotational speed encoders (±5 RPM). Blood analog fluid (glycerol-water 36% w/w) rheology characterized at 37°C. All 5 operating points replicated in triplicate. Gradation 2 achieved: test conditions documented with measurement uncertainty."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/output-comparison-mrl2",
      "rationale": "Quantitative comparison performed using validation metric (E = (M - D)/D) for hemolysis index at all 5 operating points. Mean absolute error 12.4%, within ±15% acceptance band. Uncertainty in both model output (numerical uncertainty) and experimental data (measurement uncertainty) propagated and reported. Gradation 3 achieved: comparison with combined uncertainty quantification and statistical significance assessment."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/qoi-relevance-mrl2",
      "rationale": "Primary QOI is the normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) and relative hemolysis index (RH). These are directly relevant to the COU decision criterion (RH < 1). Secondary QOI includes shear stress distribution and exposure time, which drive the power-law hemolysis model. All QOIs are standard metrics in FDA guidance for blood-contacting device CFD. Gradation 2 achieved: QOIs directly linked to COU decision criterion with documented justification."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/validation-relevance-mrl2",
      "rationale": "Validation activities conducted on the FDA generic centrifugal pump geometry under flow conditions spanning the full CPB operating envelope (2–6 L/min, 3000–5000 RPM). Blood analog fluid properties match clinical blood rheology within documented bounds. Geometric similarity between validation model and COU device confirmed by dimensional analysis. Gradation 2 achieved: validation activities directly representative of COU conditions."
    },
    {
